<h1>Jack Baty</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://baty.net/now/">baty.net/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Grand Rapids
MI
United States
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Partner and development manager at Fusionary Media
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
By day I manage web development projects and by night I take photos and tinker with analog tools.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
I'm fascinated by things both online and off. I want to explore tomorrow's tech while continuing to use and promote older analog tools and methods.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
Nothing profound, certainly. I worry that with all the conveniences of modern digital devices, we're losing something important. I don't yet know what that is but I believe it's important to find out. There are things we shouldn't forget.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
The Pleasures of Reading in an Age of Distraction by Alan Jacobs
</p>

